1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,019
Welcome to the Personalized Wound Healing
Action Plan.

2
00:00:03,019 --> 00:00:07,586
This practice helps you choose one small
healing action connected to a wound

3
00:00:07,586 --> 00:00:09,474
pattern you have been noticing.

4
00:00:09,474 --> 00:00:12,121
You do not need to fix the whole wound
today.

5
00:00:12,121 --> 00:00:15,279
You are choosing one compassionate next
step.

6
00:00:15,279 --> 00:00:17,415
Begin by settling your body.

7
00:00:17,415 --> 00:00:19,830
Take a slow breath in.

8
00:00:28,830 --> 00:00:28,830
<break time="3s" />

9
00:00:28,830 --> 00:00:30,316
And let it out.

10
00:00:30,316 --> 00:00:36,864
Now gently ask: What wound pattern has
been most present for me recently?

11
00:00:48,864 --> 00:00:48,864
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

12
00:00:48,864 --> 00:00:54,678
Maybe abandonment, shame, neglect,
betrayal, rejection, helplessness, or

13
00:00:54,678 --> 00:00:56,480
another painful theme.

14
00:00:56,480 --> 00:00:59,870
Choose one pattern to focus on today.

15
00:00:59,870 --> 00:01:05,396
Now ask: How does this wound show up in
my daily life?

16
00:01:17,396 --> 00:01:17,396
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

17
00:01:17,396 --> 00:01:22,705
Maybe in relationships, work, avoidance,
perfectionism, people pleasing,

18
00:01:22,705 --> 00:01:26,220
withdrawal, self-criticism, urgency, or
numbing.

19
00:01:26,220 --> 00:01:27,845
Notice without judgment.

20
00:01:27,845 --> 00:01:33,186
Now ask: What part of me carries this
wound most strongly?

21
00:01:45,186 --> 00:01:45,186
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

22
00:01:45,186 --> 00:01:47,508
Let a part come forward if it wants to.

23
00:01:47,508 --> 00:01:51,409
Ask this part: What do you need me to
understand?

24
00:02:03,409 --> 00:02:03,409
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

25
00:02:03,409 --> 00:02:04,477
Listen.

26
00:02:22,477 --> 00:02:22,477
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

27
00:02:22,477 --> 00:02:27,493
Now ask: What protector parts try to
prevent this wound from being felt?

28
00:02:39,493 --> 00:02:39,493
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

29
00:02:39,493 --> 00:02:44,131
Maybe a manager part, a critic, a
planner, a controller, an avoidant part,

30
00:02:44,131 --> 00:02:46,227
a firefighter, or a numbing part.

31
00:02:46,227 --> 00:02:49,013
Thank the protectors for trying to help.

32
00:02:49,013 --> 00:02:52,078
Now choose one small healing action for
this week.

33
00:02:52,078 --> 00:02:53,703
It should be simple.

34
00:02:53,703 --> 00:02:58,040
It might be pausing before
self-criticism, writing one kind sentence

35
00:02:58,040 --> 00:03:02,830
to a younger part, setting one small
boundary, practicing one breath before

36
00:03:02,830 --> 00:03:08,138
reacting, noticing when a protector shows
up, doing one Inner System Map update, or

37
00:03:08,138 --> 00:03:10,792
completing one Life Integration practice.

38
00:03:10,792 --> 00:03:14,786
Now ask: What support do I need to take
this action?

39
00:03:26,786 --> 00:03:26,786
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

40
00:03:26,786 --> 00:03:29,433
And: What part might resist this action?

41
00:03:41,433 --> 00:03:41,433
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

42
00:03:41,433 --> 00:03:41,990
Listen.

43
00:03:59,990 --> 00:03:59,990
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

44
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:03,287
Now create a gentle plan.

45
00:04:03,287 --> 00:04:09,789
When I notice this wound pattern, I will
pause and offer one small action of care.

46
00:04:09,789 --> 00:04:11,972
Let the action be realistic.

47
00:04:11,972 --> 00:04:13,458
Let it be kind.

48
00:04:13,458 --> 00:04:15,826
Let it be small enough to do.

49
00:04:15,826 --> 00:04:18,055
Take a slow breath in.

50
00:04:27,055 --> 00:04:27,055
<break time="3s" />

51
00:04:27,055 --> 00:04:28,588
And let it out.

52
00:04:28,588 --> 00:04:31,421
Thank the parts that showed up.

53
00:04:31,421 --> 00:04:34,904
You are not healing everything at once.

54
00:04:34,904 --> 00:04:37,969
You are building trust one step at a
time.

